race.comment: KID BILLY (6) let down nicely and second-up was too good for a Maiden field over 1400m at Taree. He's an improved galloper and looks capable of making it two on the trot. PATRIOTICINTENTION (3) has placed both starts this preparation and didn't have much luck at Murwillumbah last time. He can jump and run today from the inside barrier and will take plenty of pegging back. PRINCE OF PROPHETS (2) resumed nicely over 1300m at Taree on January 30. Settled back and was closing off nicely. Will be fitter for the run and has won second up in the past. HIGHLAND HUSTLE (13) next. Will be better up over a bit more ground however has placed first up in the past.
